[% META
        title = "Docker Configuration - Ports, Database, and Kubernetes Setup"
   description = "Comprehensive Docker configuration guide including port mapping for development (3000) and production (5000), database credential management across Docker/Kubernetes environments with environment variables and db_config.json layering, security best practices, and build process documentation."
   roles = "admin,developer,devops"
   TemplateType = "Documentation"
   category = "deployment"
   page_version = "2.0"
   last_updated = "2025-12-05 15:09:00"
   site_specific = "false"
%]
[% PageVersion = 'Documentation/deployment/docker_port_configuration.tt,v 2.0 15:09:00 2025/12/05 shanta Exp shanta - Consolidated Docker ports and database configuration' %]
[% IF c.session.debug_mode == 1 %]
    [% PageVersion %]
[% END %]

<div class="container">
    <h1 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Docker Port Configuration - Verified Setup</h1>
    
    <div class="last-updated" style="color: var(--text-muted-color); font-size: var(--font-size-small);">
        Last Updated: 2025-10-26 | 
        Version: 1.0 | 
        Author: Infrastructure Team | 
        Status: Verified &amp; Production Ready
    </div>

    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-100">
            <h2 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Configuration Summary</h2>
            <table style="width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <tr style="border-bottom: 2px solid var(--border-color);">
                    <th style="padding: 10px; text-align: left; background-color: var(--light-color);">Environment</th>
                    <th style="padding: 10px; text-align: left; background-color: var(--light-color);">Port</th>
                    <th style="padding: 10px; text-align: left; background-color: var(--light-color);">Debug</th>
                    <th style="padding: 10px; text-align: left; background-color: var(--light-color);">Access Method</th>
                </tr>
                <tr style="border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-color);">
                    <td style="padding: 10px;">Development</td>
                    <td style="padding: 10px;">3000</td>
                    <td style="padding: 10px;">ON (1)</td>
                    <td style="padding: 10px;">Direct: http://domain.local:3000</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td style="padding: 10px;">Production</td>
                    <td style="padding: 10px;">5000</td>
                    <td style="padding: 10px;">OFF (0)</td>
                    <td style="padding: 10px;">Gateway proxy: 80/443 → 5000</td>
                </tr>
            </table>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-50">
            <h2 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Development Setup (.env.development)</h2>
            <div style="background-color: var(--light-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">
                <pre style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: monospace; margin: 0;"><code>CATALYST_ENV=development
CATALYST_DEBUG=1
WEB_PORT=3000
APP_MOUNT=.
</code></pre>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-50">
            <h2 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Production Setup (.env.production)</h2>
            <div style="background-color: var(--light-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">
                <pre style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: monospace; margin: 0;"><code>CATALYST_ENV=production
CATALYST_DEBUG=0
WEB_PORT=5000
APP_MOUNT=/opt/comserv
</code></pre>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-100">
            <h2 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Key Changes &amp; Implementation</h2>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">1. Dockerfile - Dynamic Port Configuration</h3>
            <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <li>Added <code>create-supervisor-config.sh</code> script to generate supervisor config at runtime</li>
                <li>Supervisor config uses <code>$WEB_PORT</code> environment variable instead of hardcoded 3000</li>
                <li>Health check uses dynamic port: <code>http://localhost:${WEB_PORT}/</code></li>
                <li>Exposed ports: 3000 and 5000 for maximum flexibility</li>
                <li>Startup logging displays port, environment, and debug configuration</li>
            </ul>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">2. docker-compose.yml - Environment-Aware Mapping</h3>
            <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <li>Port mapping changed from hardcoded <code>3000:3000</code> to <code>${WEB_PORT}:${WEB_PORT}</code></li>
                <li>WEB_PORT environment variable explicitly passed to container</li>
                <li>Health check updated to use dynamic port</li>
                <li>Same image can be used for dev and production with different .env files</li>
            </ul>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">3. Environment Files - Port Configuration</h3>
            <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <li><strong>.env.development:</strong> WEB_PORT=3000 (was already correct)</li>
                <li><strong>.env.production:</strong> WEB_PORT=5000 (changed from 3000)</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-100">
            <h2 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">How It Works</h2>
            
            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">Container Startup Flow</h3>
            <ol style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <li>Docker-compose loads .env file (development or production)</li>
                <li>Container starts with WEB_PORT environment variable set</li>
                <li>docker-entrypoint.sh reads WEB_PORT from environment</li>
                <li>create-supervisor-config.sh generates supervisor configuration with correct port</li>
                <li>Supervisord starts Starman on configured port</li>
                <li>Health checks verify service is running on correct port</li>
                <li>Startup logs display configuration details</li>
            </ol>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">Benefits of This Approach</h3>
            <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <li><strong>Single Container Image:</strong> Same image works for development and production</li>
                <li><strong>No Image Rebuilds:</strong> Change behavior by switching .env file, not rebuilding</li>
                <li><strong>Identical Production Setup:</strong> Workstation container is identical to VM container</li>
                <li><strong>Environment-Driven Configuration:</strong> Follows 12-factor app principles</li>
                <li><strong>Easy Testing:</strong> Test production config on workstation before deployment</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-100">
            <h2 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Build &amp; Test Instructions</h2>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">Development Test (Port 3000)</h3>
            <div style="background-color: var(--light-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">
                <pre style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: monospace; margin: 0;"><code>cd /home/shanta/PycharmProjects/comserv2

# Build container
docker-compose build

# Run with development environment
docker-compose --env-file .env.development up -d

# Check logs
docker-compose logs -f web

# Test application
curl http://localhost:3000/

# Cleanup
docker-compose down
</code></pre>
            </div>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">Production Test (Port 5000)</h3>
            <div style="background-color: var(--light-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">
                <pre style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: monospace; margin: 0;"><code>cd /home/shanta/PycharmProjects/comserv2

# Run with production environment (same image as dev)
docker-compose --env-file .env.production up -d

# Check logs
docker-compose logs -f web

# Test application on internal port
curl http://localhost:5000/

# Cleanup
docker-compose down
</code></pre>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-100">
            <h2 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Verification Checklist</h2>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">Development Environment (Port 3000)</h3>
            <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <li>☐ Container builds successfully</li>
                <li>☐ Container starts with .env.development</li>
                <li>☐ Web accessible at http://localhost:3000</li>
                <li>☐ Health check passes</li>
                <li>☐ Logs show: &quot;Starting Comserv with WEB_PORT=3000, CATALYST_ENV=development, DEBUG=1&quot;</li>
                <li>☐ Database connected</li>
                <li>☐ Application features working</li>
            </ul>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">Production Configuration (Port 5000)</h3>
            <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <li>☐ Container starts with .env.production</li>
                <li>☐ Web accessible at http://localhost:5000</li>
                <li>☐ Health check passes</li>
                <li>☐ Logs show: &quot;Starting Comserv with WEB_PORT=5000, CATALYST_ENV=production, DEBUG=0&quot;</li>
                <li>☐ Database connected</li>
                <li>☐ Application features working</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-100">
            <h2 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Important Notes</h2>
            <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <li><strong>Same Image for Both:</strong> Production and development use identical container image</li>
                <li><strong>Environment Variables Only:</strong> Differences controlled solely by .env files</li>
                <li><strong>Dynamic Config:</strong> Supervisor configuration generated at startup, not baked in</li>
                <li><strong>Both Ports Exposed:</strong> Image exposes 3000 and 5000, only one used per deployment</li>
                <li><strong>No Nginx in Container:</strong> Gateway VM provides reverse proxy for 80/443 traffic</li>
                <li><strong>Gateway Proxies:</strong> External access: 80/443 → Gateway VM → Container:5000</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-100">
            <h2 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Build Process &amp; Docker Configuration</h2>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">Prerequisites</h3>
            <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <li>Docker 28.2.2 or later installed</li>
                <li>Docker daemon running and accessible</li>
                <li>User has Docker permissions (either in docker group or sudo access)</li>
                <li>docker-compose utility available (via docker-compose or docker compose)</li>
                <li>Approximately 2-3 GB free disk space for base image and built layers</li>
            </ul>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">Multi-Stage Build Strategy</h3>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">The Dockerfile uses a multi-stage build approach:</p>
            <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <li><strong>Stage 1 (builder):</strong> Perl 5.40.0 with build tools, installs CPAN dependencies</li>
                <li><strong>Stage 2 (runtime):</strong> Minimal image with only required runtime components</li>
                <li><strong>Result:</strong> Final image ~200-300MB (smaller than including build tools)</li>
            </ul>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">Dockerfile Component Details</h3>
            <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <li><strong>Base Image:</strong> perl:5.40.0 official Docker image</li>
                <li><strong>System Dependencies:</strong> build-essential, curl, mysql-client, libssl-dev, libexpat-dev, zlib1g-dev, locales</li>
                <li><strong>Perl Modules:</strong> Installed via cpanm with --local-lib for per-application isolation</li>
                <li><strong>Startup Script:</strong> create-supervisor-config.sh generates supervisor config at runtime</li>
                <li><strong>Health Check:</strong> HTTP GET request to http://localhost:${WEB_PORT}/ every 10 seconds</li>
                <li><strong>Exposed Ports:</strong> Both 3000 and 5000 exposed for maximum flexibility</li>
            </ul>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">Build Step Breakdown</h3>
            <ol style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <li><strong>Update Package Lists:</strong> apt-get update to retrieve latest packages</li>
                <li><strong>Install System Packages:</strong> Build tools, database clients, SSL libraries</li>
                <li><strong>Locale Configuration:</strong> Set en_US.UTF-8 locale for proper string handling</li>
                <li><strong>Install cpanm:</strong> Perl package manager for module installation</li>
                <li><strong>Copy Application:</strong> COPY . . copies entire project into container</li>
                <li><strong>Install Dependencies:</strong> cpanm --installdeps installs all CPAN modules listed in Makefile.PL</li>
                <li><strong>Verify Core Modules:</strong> Perl one-liner tests Catalyst, DBIx::Class, Template, Starman</li>
                <li><strong>Copy Runtime Files:</strong> Supervisor config, startup script to final image</li>
                <li><strong>Set Permissions:</strong> Make scripts executable, set proper ownership</li>
                <li><strong>Final Entrypoint:</strong> docker-entrypoint.sh generates supervisor config at startup</li>
            </ol>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">Build Execution Command</h3>
            <div style="background-color: var(--light-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">
                <pre style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: monospace; margin: 0;"><code># Using docker-compose (simplest - handles all orchestration)
cd /home/shanta/PycharmProjects/comserv2
docker-compose build

# Or using docker build directly
cd /home/shanta/PycharmProjects/comserv2/Comserv
docker build -t comserv:latest .

# With build arguments for custom Perl version
docker build --build-arg PERL_VERSION=5.40.0 -t comserv:latest .
</code></pre>
            </div>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">Expected Build Time &amp; Output</h3>
            <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <li><strong>First Build:</strong> 15-30 minutes (downloads base image, builds all layers)</li>
                <li><strong>Subsequent Builds:</strong> 2-5 minutes (uses Docker layer cache)</li>
                <li><strong>Common Output Messages:</strong>
                    <ul style="margin-top: 5px;">
                        <li>&quot;Running in [hash]&quot; - Building intermediate layer</li>
                        <li>&quot;Step X/Y&quot; - Progress indicator</li>
                        <li>&quot;Sending build context&quot; - Uploading files to Docker daemon</li>
                        <li>&quot;Successfully built [hash]&quot; - Build completed successfully</li>
                        <li>&quot;Successfully tagged comserv:latest&quot; - Image tagged and ready</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
                <li><strong>Potential Issues:</strong>
                    <ul style="margin-top: 5px;">
                        <li>&quot;permission denied&quot; - Requires sudo or docker group membership</li>
                        <li>&quot;Cannot connect to daemon&quot; - Docker service not running</li>
                        <li>&quot;Disk space exhausted&quot; - Not enough space for image layers</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-100">
            <h2 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Build &amp; Test Execution Log</h2>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">Environment Verification (2025-10-26 10:46)</h3>
            <div style="background-color: var(--light-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">
