                <li>✓ docker-compose.yml properly configured</li>
                <li>✓ All environment files (.env.development, .env.production) correctly set</li>
                <li>✓ create-supervisor-config.sh script in place</li>
                <li>⚠ Docker daemon socket requires elevated permissions (sudo or docker group)</li>
            </ul>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">Next Steps for Build Execution</h3>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">To complete the Docker build and testing process:</p>
            <ol style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <li><strong>Grant Docker Permissions:</strong>
                    <div style="background-color: var(--light-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); margin: 5px 0;">
                        <pre style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: monospace; margin: 0;"><code># Option 1: Add user to docker group (recommended)
sudo usermod -aG docker $USER
newgrp docker

# Option 2: Use sudo for each command
sudo docker-compose build
</code></pre>
                    </div>
                </li>
                <li><strong>Execute Build:</strong>
                    <div style="background-color: var(--light-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); margin: 5px 0;">
                        <pre style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: monospace; margin: 0;"><code>cd /home/shanta/PycharmProjects/comserv2
docker-compose build
</code></pre>
                    </div>
                </li>
                <li><strong>Test Development (Port 3000):</strong>
                    <div style="background-color: var(--light-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); margin: 5px 0;">
                        <pre style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: monospace; margin: 0;"><code>docker-compose --env-file .env.development up -d
docker-compose logs -f web
curl http://localhost:3000/
</code></pre>
                    </div>
                </li>
                <li><strong>Test Production (Port 5000):</strong>
                    <div style="background-color: var(--light-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); margin: 5px 0;">
                        <pre style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: monospace; margin: 0;"><code>docker-compose --env-file .env.production up -d
docker-compose logs -f web
curl http://localhost:5000/
</code></pre>
                    </div>
                </li>
            </ol>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-100">
            <h2 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Database Configuration for Docker & Kubernetes</h2>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">Comprehensive guide for managing database credentials and connections across development, testing, and production environments using Docker and Kubernetes.</p>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">Configuration Layers (Priority Order)</h3>
            <ol style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <li><strong>Environment Variables</strong> (COMSERV_DB_*) - Highest priority, overrides all</li>
                <li><strong>db_config.json</strong> - Base configuration, mounted/copied into container</li>
                <li><strong>Connection Priority Failover</strong> - Production → ZeroTier → Local → Backup → SQLite</li>
            </ol>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">Environment Variable Pattern</h3>
            <div style="background-color: var(--light-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">
                <pre style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: monospace; margin: 0;"><code>COMSERV_DB_&lt;CONNECTION_NAME&gt;_&lt;FIELD&gt;=value

Examples:
COMSERV_DB_PRODUCTION_SERVER_HOST=192.168.1.198
COMSERV_DB_LOCAL_ENCY_HOST=database
COMSERV_DB_LOCAL_ENCY_USERNAME=comserv
</code></pre>
            </div>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">db_config.json Structure</h3>
            <div style="background-color: var(--light-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">
                <pre style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: monospace; margin: 0;"><code>{
  "connection_name": {
    "db_type": "mysql",
    "host": "hostname",
    "port": 3306,
    "username": "user",
    "password": "pass",
    "database": "dbname",
    "priority": 1
  }
}
</code></pre>
            </div>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">Docker Compose Environment Setup</h3>
            <div style="background-color: var(--light-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">
                <pre style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: monospace; margin: 0;"><code>services:
  web:
    environment:
      - COMSERV_DB_LOCAL_ENCY_HOST=database
      - COMSERV_DB_LOCAL_ENCY_PORT=3306
      - COMSERV_DB_LOCAL_ENCY_USERNAME=comserv
      - COMSERV_DB_LOCAL_ENCY_PASSWORD=comserv_pass
    volumes:
      - ./db_config.json:/opt/comserv/db_config.json:ro
      
  database:
    image: mysql:8.0
    environment:
      MYSQL_ROOT_PASSWORD: root_password
      MYSQL_USER: comserv
      MYSQL_PASSWORD: comserv_pass
</code></pre>
            </div>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">Kubernetes Deployment Example</h3>
            <div style="background-color: var(--light-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">
                <pre style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: monospace; margin: 0;"><code>apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: comserv-app
spec:
  containers:
  - name: web
    image: comserv:latest
    env:
    - name: COMSERV_DB_PRODUCTION_SERVER_HOST
      value: "comserv-database.production.svc.cluster.local"
    - name: COMSERV_DB_PRODUCTION_SERVER_USERNAME
      valueFrom:
        secretKeyRef:
          name: comserv-db-credentials
          key: username
    volumeMounts:
    - name: db-config
      mountPath: /opt/comserv/db_config.json
      subPath: db_config.json
</code></pre>
            </div>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">Security Best Practices</h3>
            <div style="background-color: #fff3cd; color: #856404; padding: var(--spacing-medium); border: 1px solid #ffeeba; border-radius: 4px; margin: var(--spacing-medium) 0;">
                <p style="margin: 0; font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>✓ Do's:</strong></p>
                <ul style="margin: 5px 0; padding-left: 20px;">
                    <li>Store credentials in environment variables</li>
                    <li>Mount db_config.json read-only</li>
                    <li>Use different credentials per environment</li>
                    <li>Use strong passwords (16+ chars)</li>
                </ul>
                <p style="margin: 10px 0 0 0; font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>❌ Don'ts:</strong></p>
                <ul style="margin: 5px 0; padding-left: 20px;">
                    <li>Commit db_config.json to git</li>
                    <li>Hardcode passwords in Dockerfiles</li>
                    <li>Log sensitive values</li>
                    <li>Expose database ports externally</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">Troubleshooting</h3>
            <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <li><strong>"Cannot continue without database configuration"</strong> - Verify db_config.json is mounted or COMSERV_DB_CONFIG env var is set</li>
                <li><strong>"Connection refused"</strong> - Verify hostname in environment variable matches Docker service name or K8s DNS</li>
                <li><strong>"Access denied for user"</strong> - Check COMSERV_DB_* credentials with <code>docker-compose exec web env | grep COMSERV_DB</code></li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-100">
            <div style="background-color: #d4edda; color: #155724; padding: var(--spacing-medium); border: 1px solid #c3e6cb; border-radius: 4px; margin: var(--spacing-medium) 0;">
                <p style="margin: 0; font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>✓ Status: Configuration Complete - Ready for User Build Execution</strong></p>
                <p style="margin: 0; font-family: var(--body-font);">All configuration files verified. Documentation complete with step-by-step build and test instructions. User should execute docker build with appropriate permissions (sudo or docker group membership).</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
